{"word":"ἄτεκνος","slug":"ἄτεκνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄτεκνος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τέκνον'><el>τέκνον</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without children, childless</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in causal sense, <i>destroying children</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}